76  - Ultra Low Power Medium-density Plus devices are STM32L151xx, STM32L152xx and

281 #if defined ( __CC_ARM )
282 /* ARM Compiler
283  ------------
284  RAM functions are defined using the toolchain options.
285  Functions that are executed in RAM should reside in a separate source
286  module. Using the 'Options for File' dialog you can simply change the
287  'Code / Const' area of a module to a memory space in physical RAM.
288  Available memory areas are declared in the 'Target' tab of the
289  'Options for Target' dialog.
290 */
291  #define __RAM_FUNC FLASH_Status
292 
293 #elif defined ( __ICCARM__ )
294 /* ICCARM Compiler
295  ---------------
296  RAM functions are defined using a specific toolchain keyword "__ramfunc".
297 */
298  #define __RAM_FUNC __ramfunc FLASH_Status
299 
300 #elif defined ( __GNUC__ )
301 /* GNU Compiler
302  ------------
303  RAM functions are defined using a specific toolchain attribute
304  "__attribute__((section(".data")))".
305 */
306  #define __RAM_FUNC FLASH_Status __attribute__((section(".data")))
307 
308 #elif defined ( __TASKING__ )
309 /* TASKING Compiler
310  ----------------
311  RAM functions are defined using a specific toolchain pragma. This pragma is
312  defined in the stm32l1xx_flash_ramfunc.c
313 */
314  #define __RAM_FUNC FLASH_Status

316 #endif

869 #define FLASH_BASE ((uint32_t)0x08000000)
870 #define SRAM_BASE ((uint32_t)0x20000000)
871 #define PERIPH_BASE ((uint32_t)0x40000000)
873 #define SRAM_BB_BASE ((uint32_t)0x22000000)
874 #define PERIPH_BB_BASE ((uint32_t)0x42000000)
876 #define FSMC_R_BASE ((uint32_t)0xA0000000)
879 #define APB1PERIPH_BASE PERIPH_BASE
880 #define APB2PERIPH_BASE (PERIPH_BASE + 0x10000)
881 #define AHBPERIPH_BASE (PERIPH_BASE + 0x20000)
882
